Christian LARSEN et al., Appellants, v. CHARLES STEAMSHIP CO., a Corporation, Claimant of the Steamship C. H. LAWRENCE, etc., Appellee. No. 6088. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth. Circuit. May 14, 1930. John J. Monahan, of San Diego, Cal., for appellants. Overton, Lyman & Plumb and L. K. Vermille, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before RUDKIN, DIETRICH, and WILBUR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

No brief being filed on behalf of appellants when the ease was regularly called for hearing, the appeal is dismissed.
